Managing and Administering a Kubernetes Cluster


Step 1: Verify the certificates of the cluster.


1.1
Run the following command to check the expiration date of the certificate as a regular user:
sudo kubeadm certs check-expiration


1.3
Run the following command to view complete cluster information on the master node:
kubectl cluster-info dump

Step 2: Create a namespace
2.1
Run the following command to create a namespace:
kubectl create namespace firstnamespace


2.2 Confirm the creation of the new namespace with the following 
command: kubectl get namespaces
Step 3: Access clusters using the Kubernetes API
3.1
Run the following command to view the cluster configuration:
kubectl config view




3.2 Run the following command to view the current cluster: kubectl 
config current-context


3.3
Execute and copy the 127.0.0.1:8080 port to identify the API server, as shown in the screenshot below:
kubectl proxy --port=8080


By following these steps, you have successfully verified cluster certifica.
